Vintage style illustration of two elaborate mechanical machines facing each other on a workbench, one sleek and compact with fewer gears and pistons, the other sprawling with an excessive array of interconnected cogs, valves, pipes, and redundant components. The complex machine takes up three times the space, with steam wisps rising from various joints. Warm sepia and brass tones dominate, with rich mahogany wood surfaces. Technical blueprint papers scattered beneath both machines. The scene evokes Victorian-era engineering comparison, with dramatic side lighting casting long shadows that emphasize the stark difference in complexity between the two contraptions.
